{
  "video_id": "_MBiP3G2Pzc",
  "title": "Steve Silberman: The forgotten history of autism",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12882.0,
      "end_time": 15482.0,
      "text": "Just after Christmas last year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15482.0,
      "end_time": 19320.0,
      "text": "132 kids in California got the measles"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19320.0,
      "end_time": 21333.0,
      "text": "by either visiting Disneyland"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21333.0,
      "end_time": 24282.0,
      "text": "or being exposed to someone who&#39;d been there."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24282.0,
      "end_time": 27486.0,
      "text": "The virus then hopped the Canadian border,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27486.0,
      "end_time": 30922.0,
      "text": "infecting more than 100 children in Quebec."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 30922.0,
      "end_time": 33871.0,
      "text": "One of the tragic things about this outbreak"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 33871.0,
      "end_time": 39490.0,
      "text": "is that measles, which can be fatal to a child with a weakened immune system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 39490.0,
      "end_time": 43275.0,
      "text": "is one of the most easily preventable diseases in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 43275.0,
      "end_time": 45272.0,
      "text": "An effective vaccine against it"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 45272.0,
      "end_time": 48638.0,
      "text": "has been available for more than half a century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 48638.0,
      "end_time": 51912.0,
      "text": "but many of the kids involved in the Disneyland outbreak"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 51912.0,
      "end_time": 53886.0,
      "text": "had not been vaccinated"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53886.0,
      "end_time": 56138.0,
      "text": "because their parents were afraid"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 56138.0,
      "end_time": 59157.0,
      "text": "of something allegedly even worse:"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 59157.0,
      "end_time": 60875.0,
      "text": "autism."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 60875.0,
      "end_time": 64658.0,
      "text": "But wait -- wasn&#39;t the paper that sparked the controversy"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 64658.0,
      "end_time": 66981.0,
      "text": "about autism and vaccines"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 66981.0,
      "end_time": 68978.0,
      "text": "debunked, retracted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 68978.0,
      "end_time": 71450.0,
      "text": "and branded a deliberate fraud"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 71450.0,
      "end_time": 73158.0,
      "text": "by the British Medical Journal?"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 73158.0,
      "end_time": 75201.0,
      "text": "Don&#39;t most science-savvy people"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 75201.0,
      "end_time": 79520.0,
      "text": "know that the theory that vaccines cause autism is B.S.?"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 79520.0,
      "end_time": 81377.0,
      "text": "I think most of you do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 81377.0,
      "end_time": 83955.0,
      "text": "but millions of parents worldwide"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 83955.0,
      "end_time": 88923.0,
      "text": "continue to fear that vaccines put their kids at risk for autism."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 88923.0,
      "end_time": 90827.0,
      "text": "Why?"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 90827.0,
      "end_time": 92290.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s why."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 92290.0,
      "end_time": 97375.0,
      "text": "This is a graph of autism prevalence estimates rising over time."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 97375.0,
      "end_time": 99488.0,
      "text": "For most of the 20th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 99488.0,
      "end_time": 103180.0,
      "text": "autism was considered an incredibly rare condition."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 103180.0,
      "end_time": 106500.0,
      "text": "The few psychologists and pediatricians who&#39;d even heard of it"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 106500.0,
      "end_time": 109217.0,
      "text": "figured they would get through their entire careers"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 109217.0,
      "end_time": 112364.0,
      "text": "without seeing a single case."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 112364.0,
      "end_time": 115602.0,
      "text": "For decades, the prevalence estimates remained stable"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 115602.0,
      "end_time": 118853.0,
      "text": "at just three or four children in 10,000."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 118853.0,
      "end_time": 120919.0,
      "text": "But then, in the 1990s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 120919.0,
      "end_time": 123380.0,
      "text": "the numbers started to skyrocket."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 123380.0,
      "end_time": 126608.0,
      "text": "Fundraising organizations like Autism Speaks"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 126608.0,
      "end_time": 129696.0,
      "text": "routinely refer to autism as an epidemic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 129696.0,
      "end_time": 133365.0,
      "text": "as if you could catch it from another kid at Disneyland."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 133365.0,
      "end_time": 134967.0,
      "text": "So what&#39;s going on?"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 134967.0,
      "end_time": 138194.0,
      "text": "If it isn&#39;t vaccines, what is it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 138194.0,
      "end_time": 142165.0,
      "text": "If you ask the folks down at the Centers for Disease Control in Atlanta"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 142165.0,
      "end_time": 143860.0,
      "text": "what&#39;s going on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 143860.0,
      "end_time": 148370.0,
      "text": "they tend to rely on phrases like &quot;broadened diagnostic criteria&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148370.0,
      "end_time": 150134.0,
      "text": "and &quot;better case finding&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 150134.0,
      "end_time": 152711.0,
      "text": "to explain these rising numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 152711.0,
      "end_time": 154731.0,
      "text": "But that kind of language"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 154731.0,
      "end_time": 157680.0,
      "text": "doesn&#39;t do much to allay the fears of a young mother"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 157680.0,
      "end_time": 162324.0,
      "text": "who is searching her two-year-old&#39;s face for eye contact."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 162324.0,
      "end_time": 165319.0,
      "text": "If the diagnostic criteria had to be broadened,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 165319.0,
      "end_time": 168152.0,
      "text": "why were they so narrow in the first place?"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 168152.0,
      "end_time": 171147.0,
      "text": "Why were cases of autism so hard to find"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 171147.0,
      "end_time": 173437.0,
      "text": "before the 1990s?"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 173437.0,
      "end_time": 179172.0,
      "text": "Five years ago, I decided to try to uncover the answers to these questions."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 179172.0,
      "end_time": 181216.0,
      "text": "I learned that what happened"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 181216.0,
      "end_time": 185116.0,
      "text": "has less to do with the slow and cautious progress of science"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 185116.0,
      "end_time": 188544.0,
      "text": "than it does with the seductive power of storytelling."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 188544.0,
      "end_time": 190750.0,
      "text": "For most of the 20th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 190750.0,
      "end_time": 193211.0,
      "text": "clinicians told one story"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 193211.0,
      "end_time": 196763.0,
      "text": "about what autism is and how it was discovered,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 196763.0,
      "end_time": 199573.0,
      "text": "but that story turned out to be wrong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 199573.0,
      "end_time": 201384.0,
      "text": "and the consequences of it"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 201384.0,
      "end_time": 205285.0,
      "text": "are having a devastating impact on global public health."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 205285.0,
      "end_time": 208814.0,
      "text": "There was a second, more accurate story of autism"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 208814.0,
      "end_time": 211430.0,
      "text": "which had been lost and forgotten"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 211430.0,
      "end_time": 214410.0,
      "text": "in obscure corners of the clinical literature."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 214410.0,
      "end_time": 218427.0,
      "text": "This second story tells us everything about how we got here"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 218427.0,
      "end_time": 221352.0,
      "text": "and where we need to go next."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 221352.0,
      "end_time": 225996.0,
      "text": "The first story starts with a child psychiatrist at Johns Hopkins Hospital"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 225996.0,
      "end_time": 227946.0,
      "text": "named Leo Kanner."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 227946.0,
      "end_time": 231499.0,
      "text": "In 1943, Kanner published a paper"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 231499.0,
      "end_time": 236212.0,
      "text": "describing 11 young patients who seemed to inhabit private worlds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 236212.0,
      "end_time": 238302.0,
      "text": "ignoring the people around them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 238302.0,
      "end_time": 240462.0,
      "text": "even their own parents."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 240462.0,
      "end_time": 242737.0,
      "text": "They could amuse themselves for hours"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 242737.0,
      "end_time": 245384.0,
      "text": "by flapping their hands in front of their faces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 245384.0,
      "end_time": 247358.0,
      "text": "but they were panicked by little things"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 247358.0,
      "end_time": 250970.0,
      "text": "like their favorite toy being moved from its usual place"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 250970.0,
      "end_time": 252977.0,
      "text": "without their knowledge."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 252977.0,
      "end_time": 255693.0,
      "text": "Based on the patients who were brought to his clinic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 255693.0,
      "end_time": 259269.0,
      "text": "Kanner speculated that autism is very rare."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 259269.0,
      "end_time": 263727.0,
      "text": "By the 1950s, as the world&#39;s leading authority on the subject,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 263727.0,
      "end_time": 269300.0,
      "text": "he declared that he had seen less than 150 true cases of his syndrome"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 269300.0,
      "end_time": 273363.0,
      "text": "while fielding referrals from as far away as South Africa."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 273363.0,
      "end_time": 275754.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s actually not surprising,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 275754.0,
      "end_time": 279130.0,
      "text": "because Kanner&#39;s criteria for diagnosing autism"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 279130.0,
      "end_time": 281443.0,
      "text": "were incredibly selective."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 281443.0,
      "end_time": 286621.0,
      "text": "For example, he discouraged giving the diagnosis to children who had seizures"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 286621.0,
      "end_time": 290382.0,
      "text": "but now we know that epilepsy is very common in autism."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 290382.0,
      "end_time": 293424.0,
      "text": "He once bragged that he had turned nine out of 10 kids"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 293424.0,
      "end_time": 297255.0,
      "text": "referred to his office as autistic by other clinicians"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 297255.0,
      "end_time": 300503.0,
      "text": "without giving them an autism diagnosis."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 300503.0,
      "end_time": 302944.0,
      "text": "Kanner was a smart guy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 302944.0,
      "end_time": 305113.0,
      "text": "but a number of his theories didn&#39;t pan out."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 305113.0,
      "end_time": 308888.0,
      "text": "He classified autism as a form of infantile psychosis"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 308888.0,
      "end_time": 312858.0,
      "text": "caused by cold and unaffectionate parents."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 312858.0,
      "end_time": 314995.0,
      "text": "These children, he said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 314995.0,
      "end_time": 319313.0,
      "text": "had been kept neatly in a refrigerator that didn&#39;t defrost."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 319313.0,
      "end_time": 321264.0,
      "text": "At the same time, however,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 321264.0,
      "end_time": 324189.0,
      "text": "Kanner noticed that some of his young patients"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 324189.0,
      "end_time": 327602.0,
      "text": "had special abilities that clustered in certain areas"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 327602.0,
      "end_time": 330853.0,
      "text": "like music, math and memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 330853.0,
      "end_time": 332734.0,
      "text": "One boy in his clinic"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 332734.0,
      "end_time": 337796.0,
      "text": "could distinguish between 18 symphonies before he turned two."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 337796.0,
      "end_time": 340443.0,
      "text": "When his mother put on one of his favorite records,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 340443.0,
      "end_time": 343809.0,
      "text": "he would correctly declare, &quot;Beethoven!&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 343809.0,
      "end_time": 346665.0,
      "text": "But Kanner took a dim view of these abilities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 346665.0,
      "end_time": 350242.0,
      "text": "claiming that the kids were just regurgitating things"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 350242.0,
      "end_time": 352865.0,
      "text": "they&#39;d heard their pompous parents say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 352865.0,
      "end_time": 355465.0,
      "text": "desperate to earn their approval."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 355465.0,
      "end_time": 360829.0,
      "text": "As a result, autism became a source of shame and stigma for families,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 360829.0,
      "end_time": 363406.0,
      "text": "and two generations of autistic children"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 363406.0,
      "end_time": 366889.0,
      "text": "were shipped off to institutions for their own good,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 366889.0,
      "end_time": 370163.0,
      "text": "becoming invisible to the world at large."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 370163.0,
      "end_time": 374400.0,
      "text": "Amazingly, it wasn&#39;t until the 1970s"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 374400.0,
      "end_time": 379567.0,
      "text": "that researchers began to test Kanner&#39;s theory that autism was rare."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 379567.0,
      "end_time": 383305.0,
      "text": "Lorna Wing was a cognitive psychologist in London"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 383305.0,
      "end_time": 386509.0,
      "text": "who thought that Kanner&#39;s theory of refrigerator parenting"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 386509.0,
      "end_time": 389528.0,
      "text": "were &quot;bloody stupid,&quot; as she told me."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 389528.0,
      "end_time": 393707.0,
      "text": "She and her husband John were warm and affectionate people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 393707.0,
      "end_time": 397110.0,
      "text": "and they had a profoundly autistic daughter named Susie."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 397110.0,
      "end_time": 401822.0,
      "text": "Lorna and John knew how hard it was to raise a child like Susie"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 401822.0,
      "end_time": 403784.0,
      "text": "without support services,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 403784.0,
      "end_time": 405386.0,
      "text": "special education,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 405386.0,
      "end_time": 409635.0,
      "text": "and the other resources that are out of reach without a diagnosis."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 409635.0,
      "end_time": 412259.0,
      "text": "To make the case to the National Health Service"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 412259.0,
      "end_time": 417507.0,
      "text": "that more resources were needed for autistic children and their families,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 417507.0,
      "end_time": 419643.0,
      "text": "Lorna and her colleague Judith Gould"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 419643.0,
      "end_time": 424193.0,
      "text": "decided to do something that should have been done 30 years earlier."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 424193.0,
      "end_time": 429139.0,
      "text": "They undertook a study of autism prevalence in the general population."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 429139.0,
      "end_time": 433435.0,
      "text": "They pounded the pavement in a London suburb called Camberwell"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 433435.0,
      "end_time": 437100.0,
      "text": "to try to find autistic children in the community."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 437100.0,
      "end_time": 441767.0,
      "text": "What they saw made clear that Kanner&#39;s model was way too narrow,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 441767.0,
      "end_time": 446663.0,
      "text": "while the reality of autism was much more colorful and diverse."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 446663.0,
      "end_time": 448806.0,
      "text": "Some kids couldn&#39;t talk at all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 448806.0,
      "end_time": 453542.0,
      "text": "while others waxed on at length about their fascination with astrophysics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 453542.0,
      "end_time": 457486.0,
      "text": "dinosaurs or the genealogy of royalty."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 457486.0,
      "end_time": 462176.0,
      "text": "In other words, these children didn&#39;t fit into nice, neat boxes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 462176.0,
      "end_time": 463871.0,
      "text": "as Judith put it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 463871.0,
      "end_time": 465752.0,
      "text": "and they saw lots of them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 465752.0,
      "end_time": 469537.0,
      "text": "way more than Kanner&#39;s monolithic model would have predicted."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 469537.0,
      "end_time": 473252.0,
      "text": "At first, they were at a loss to make sense of their data."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 473252.0,
      "end_time": 476380.0,
      "text": "How had no one noticed these children before?"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 476380.0,
      "end_time": 479899.0,
      "text": "But then Lorna came upon a reference to a paper that had been published"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 479899.0,
      "end_time": 482554.0,
      "text": "in German in 1944,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 482554.0,
      "end_time": 484899.0,
      "text": "the year after Kanner&#39;s paper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 484899.0,
      "end_time": 486617.0,
      "text": "and then forgotten,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 486617.0,
      "end_time": 489194.0,
      "text": "buried with the ashes of a terrible time"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 489194.0,
      "end_time": 492445.0,
      "text": "that no one wanted to remember or think about."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 492445.0,
      "end_time": 495115.0,
      "text": "Kanner knew about this competing paper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 495115.0,
      "end_time": 499860.0,
      "text": "but scrupulously avoided mentioning it in his own work."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 499860.0,
      "end_time": 502322.0,
      "text": "It had never even been translated into English,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 502322.0,
      "end_time": 505285.0,
      "text": "but luckily, Lorna&#39;s husband spoke German,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 505285.0,
      "end_time": 507932.0,
      "text": "and he translated it for her."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 507932.0,
      "end_time": 511624.0,
      "text": "The paper offered an alternate story of autism."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 511624.0,
      "end_time": 514317.0,
      "text": "Its author was a man named Hans Asperger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 514317.0,
      "end_time": 517591.0,
      "text": "who ran a combination clinic and residential school"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 517591.0,
      "end_time": 520331.0,
      "text": "in Vienna in the 1930s."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 520331.0,
      "end_time": 524302.0,
      "text": "Asperger&#39;s ideas about teaching children with learning differences"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 524302.0,
      "end_time": 527436.0,
      "text": "were progressive even by contemporary standards."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 527436.0,
      "end_time": 531848.0,
      "text": "Mornings at his clinic began with exercise classes set to music,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 531848.0,
      "end_time": 535354.0,
      "text": "and the children put on plays on Sunday afternoons."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 535354.0,
      "end_time": 538349.0,
      "text": "Instead of blaming parents for causing autism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 538349.0,
      "end_time": 543202.0,
      "text": "Asperger framed it as a lifelong, polygenetic disability"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 543202.0,
      "end_time": 547103.0,
      "text": "that requires compassionate forms of support and accommodations"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 547103.0,
      "end_time": 550510.0,
      "text": "over the course of one&#39;s whole life."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 550510.0,
      "end_time": 553395.0,
      "text": "Rather than treating the kids in his clinic like patients,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 553395.0,
      "end_time": 556460.0,
      "text": "Asperger called them his little professors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 556460.0,
      "end_time": 560245.0,
      "text": "and enlisted their help in developing methods of education"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 560245.0,
      "end_time": 562729.0,
      "text": "that were particularly suited to them."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 562729.0,
      "end_time": 568460.0,
      "text": "Crucially, Asperger viewed autism as a diverse continuum"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 568460.0,
      "end_time": 573584.0,
      "text": "that spans an astonishing range of giftedness and disability."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 573584.0,
      "end_time": 577116.0,
      "text": "He believed that autism and autistic traits are common"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 577116.0,
      "end_time": 578982.0,
      "text": "and always have been,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 578982.0,
      "end_time": 584276.0,
      "text": "seeing aspects of this continuum in familiar archetypes from pop culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 584276.0,
      "end_time": 586612.0,
      "text": "like the socially awkward scientist"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 586612.0,
      "end_time": 589306.0,
      "text": "and the absent-minded professor."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 589306.0,
      "end_time": 591419.0,
      "text": "He went so far as to say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 591419.0,
      "end_time": 594646.0,
      "text": "it seems that for success in science and art,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 594646.0,
      "end_time": 598292.0,
      "text": "a dash of autism is essential."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 598292.0,
      "end_time": 603214.0,
      "text": "Lorna and Judith realized that Kanner had been as wrong about autism being rare"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 603214.0,
      "end_time": 605907.0,
      "text": "as he had been about parents causing it."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 605907.0,
      "end_time": 607951.0,
      "text": "Over the next several years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 607951.0,
      "end_time": 611364.0,
      "text": "they quietly worked with the American Psychiatric Association"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 611364.0,
      "end_time": 613964.0,
      "text": "to broaden the criteria for diagnosis"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 613964.0,
      "end_time": 617981.0,
      "text": "to reflect the diversity of what they called &quot;the autism spectrum.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 617981.0,
      "end_time": 620559.0,
      "text": "In the late &#39;80s and early 1990s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 620559.0,
      "end_time": 622857.0,
      "text": "their changes went into effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 622857.0,
      "end_time": 625226.0,
      "text": "swapping out Kanner&#39;s narrow model"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 625226.0,
      "end_time": 628801.0,
      "text": "for Asperger&#39;s broad and inclusive one."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 628801.0,
      "end_time": 631472.0,
      "text": "These changes weren&#39;t happening in a vacuum."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 631472.0,
      "end_time": 635326.0,
      "text": "By coincidence, as Lorna and Judith worked behind the scenes"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 635326.0,
      "end_time": 637160.0,
      "text": "to reform the criteria,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 637160.0,
      "end_time": 642176.0,
      "text": "people all over the world were seeing an autistic adult for the first time."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 642176.0,
      "end_time": 645550.0,
      "text": "Before &quot;Rain Man&quot; came out in 1988,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 645550.0,
      "end_time": 650209.0,
      "text": "only a tiny, ingrown circle of experts knew what autism looked like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 650209.0,
      "end_time": 654969.0,
      "text": "but after Dustin Hoffman&#39;s unforgettable performance as Raymond Babbitt"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 654969.0,
      "end_time": 658104.0,
      "text": "earned &quot;Rain Man&quot; four Academy Awards,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 658104.0,
      "end_time": 660844.0,
      "text": "pediatricians, psychologists,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 660844.0,
      "end_time": 665534.0,
      "text": "teachers and parents all over the world knew what autism looked like."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 665534.0,
      "end_time": 668459.0,
      "text": "Coincidentally, at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 668459.0,
      "end_time": 673939.0,
      "text": "the first easy-to-use clinical tests for diagnosing autism were introduced."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 673939.0,
      "end_time": 678629.0,
      "text": "You no longer had to have a connection to that tiny circle of experts"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 678629.0,
      "end_time": 681207.0,
      "text": "to get your child evaluated."
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 681207.0,
      "end_time": 683320.0,
      "text": "The combination of &quot;Rain Man,&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 683320.0,
      "end_time": 687499.0,
      "text": "the changes to the criteria, and the introduction of these tests"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 687499.0,
      "end_time": 689774.0,
      "text": "created a network effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 689774.0,
      "end_time": 693304.0,
      "text": "a perfect storm of autism awareness."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 693304.0,
      "end_time": 696322.0,
      "text": "The number of diagnoses started to soar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 696322.0,
      "end_time": 701990.0,
      "text": "just as Lorna and Judith predicted, indeed hoped, that it would,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 701990.0,
      "end_time": 704106.0,
      "text": "enabling autistic people and their families"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 704106.0,
      "end_time": 707798.0,
      "text": "to finally get the support and services they deserved."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 707798.0,
      "end_time": 709864.0,
      "text": "Then Andrew Wakefield came along"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 709864.0,
      "end_time": 713719.0,
      "text": "to blame the spike in diagnoses on vaccines,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 713719.0,
      "end_time": 715832.0,
      "text": "a simple, powerful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 715832.0,
      "end_time": 718618.0,
      "text": "and seductively believable story"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 718618.0,
      "end_time": 720986.0,
      "text": "that was as wrong as Kanner&#39;s theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 720986.0,
      "end_time": 723239.0,
      "text": "that autism was rare."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 723239.0,
      "end_time": 726710.0,
      "text": "If the CDC&#39;s current estimate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 726710.0,
      "end_time": 731133.0,
      "text": "that one in 68 kids in America are on the spectrum, is correct,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 731133.0,
      "end_time": 735340.0,
      "text": "autistics are one of the largest minority groups in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 735340.0,
      "end_time": 739167.0,
      "text": "In recent years, autistic people have come together on the Internet"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 739167.0,
      "end_time": 742812.0,
      "text": "to reject the notion that they are puzzles to be solved"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 742812.0,
      "end_time": 744995.0,
      "text": "by the next medical breakthrough,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 744995.0,
      "end_time": 747456.0,
      "text": "coining the term &quot;neurodiversity&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 747456.0,
      "end_time": 751264.0,
      "text": "to celebrate the varieties of human cognition."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 751264.0,
      "end_time": 753655.0,
      "text": "One way to understand neurodiversity"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 753655.0,
      "end_time": 757324.0,
      "text": "is to think in terms of human operating systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 757324.0,
      "end_time": 762240.0,
      "text": "Just because a P.C. is not running Windows doesn&#39;t mean that it&#39;s broken."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 762240.0,
      "end_time": 765869.0,
      "text": "By autistic standards, the normal human brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 765869.0,
      "end_time": 767889.0,
      "text": "is easily distractable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 767889.0,
      "end_time": 769677.0,
      "text": "obsessively social,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 769677.0,
      "end_time": 772997.0,
      "text": "and suffers from a deficit of attention to detail."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 772997.0,
      "end_time": 775992.0,
      "text": "To be sure, autistic people have a hard time"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 775992.0,
      "end_time": 778268.0,
      "text": "living in a world not built for them."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 778268.0,
      "end_time": 782520.0,
      "text": "[Seventy] years later, we&#39;re still catching up to Asperger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 782520.0,
      "end_time": 786603.0,
      "text": "who believed that the &quot;cure&quot; for the most disabling aspects of autism"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 786603.0,
      "end_time": 789529.0,
      "text": "is to be found in understanding teachers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 789529.0,
      "end_time": 791665.0,
      "text": "accommodating employers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 791665.0,
      "end_time": 793522.0,
      "text": "supportive communities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 793522.0,
      "end_time": 796866.0,
      "text": "and parents who have faith in their children&#39;s potential."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 796866.0,
      "end_time": 799908.0,
      "text": "An autistic woman named Zosia Zaks once said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 799908.0,
      "end_time": 805211.0,
      "text": "&quot;We need all hands on deck to right the ship of humanity.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 805211.0,
      "end_time": 807764.0,
      "text": "As we sail into an uncertain future,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 807764.0,
      "end_time": 811502.0,
      "text": "we need every form of human intelligence on the planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 811502.0,
      "end_time": 817469.0,
      "text": "working together to tackle the challenges that we face as a society."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 817469.0,
      "end_time": 819791.0,
      "text": "We can&#39;t afford to waste a brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 819791.0,
      "end_time": 822136.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 822136.0,
      "end_time": 832136.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}